<section id="{{ slugify title }}">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-lg-12">
			<h1>{{ title }}</h1>
			{{#markdown}}{{ description }}{{/markdown}}
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="row">
		{{#each photographs }}
		<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
			{{> image this }}
			<br/>
		</div>
		{{/each}}
		<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
			<h3>Text on photo</h3>
			<p>A word or a short sentence can be written directly on a photo. Longer copy should be written on either a white or color background. However, exceptions can be made. A photo of a concrete wall for example will probably make a descent background for longer copy as well.</p>
			<h3>Readability</h3>
			<p>Text on a photo can be a nice visual touch but defeat its purpose if the text is not readable. If thereâ€™s too much distraction in the image you will lose the readability. Have this in mind when choosing photo and whether putting the text directly on the photo or in a box.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
			{{> image "./images/readable.jpg" }}
			<br/>
		</div>
		<div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
			{{> image "./images/not-readable.jpg" }}
			<br/>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-lg-12">
			<hr/>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>